  "text": "Our starting point to model NF-κB signaling was the detailed kinetic model published by Lipniacki and colleagues [CITATION_1] . This model quantitatively describes the molecular processes that transduce an extracellular TNF signal into a change in nuclear NF-κB concentrations. The model accounts for transient TNF-dependent IKK activation, NF-κB-regulated target gene expression (cgen-mRNA), and the inhibitory actions of IκB and A20 on NF-κB activation ( Figure 1 ). The parameters used in the model have either been measured or good estimates have been derived to quantitatively describe the temporal changes observed in concentrations of pathway components in experiments [CITATION_2] .",
